<TEXT>
thor a 450pound pet bear who wasnt 
wanted in the suburbs has moved to the country 
sunday was the deadline bloomington officials had given thors 
owners charles and deborah crosby to move the bear from his 
backyard home in the minneapolis suburb officials had cited a city 
ordinance prohibiting wild animals 
thor was moved quietly friday night to a new home the couple 
built on 12 acres outside of city limits crosbys mother said 
sunday 
we miss him terribly said walterine crosby who referred to 
herself as thors grandma 
the bears new den is made of earthbanked logs and features a 
40foot by 40foot cage and a pond near the crosbys new home the 
nearest neighbors are miles away 
the bloomington city council first tried to banish thor last 
fall after someone called city hall to report the bear officials 
ordered the crosbys to get rid of thor but the order was delayed 
because the bear was hibernating in a fencedin den and nobody 
wanted to wake him up 
the crosbys who got thor as a 5weekold cub from a game farm 
have said the now 3yearold bear has never hurt anyone his front 
claws have been removed and hes been trained to respond to the 
command dont touch 
</TEXT>
