<TEXT>
at least two groups are planning to bid 
against charlotte sports executive george shinn to buy heritage 
usa the theme park of the strapped ptl ministry a newspaper 
reported sunday 
it was disclosed last week that ptl officials were discussing a 
sale of assets to shinn that would allow the ministry built by jim 
and tammy bakker to maintain control of its church activities 
the charlotte observer reported sunday that some ptl creditors 
doubting shinns willingness to provide upfront cash in his bid 
is seeking a group of buyers more to their liking the group 
includes among others first city bank of minneapolis the 
newspaper reported 
cash up front is better than promised cash the newspaper 
quoted an unidentified source as saying they think they can put 
together a better package 
also a new salt lake city corporation tango trading co whose 
principals include former ptl vice president dale hill has 
announced it will bid for heritage usa 
ptl spokesman david west said saturday that ministry officials 
have talked with a tulsa okla group of christian people with 
resources interested in refinancing ptl so it wont have to sell 
heritage usa west wouldnt name members of the group 
in us bankruptcy court monday ptl will file a plan to spin 
off its tv ministry and put the heritage usa christian retreat up 
for sale to pay debts that could amount to 130 million 
the charlotte observer reported last week that shinn talked with 
ministry officials about taking over the heritage grand hotel the 
theme park and ptls 1700 acres of undeveloped land 
shinn also might buy the ministrys tv studio church and 
amphitheater and lease them back to a reorganized taxexempt 
ministry to be called heritage ministries the observer said 
the proposal is contingent on york county building a 12 million 
sports complex including a stadium for shinns class aa baseball 
team and a training center for his charlotte hornets which join 
the national basketball association next year the york county 
council is expected to discuss financing options on monday 
shinn says no price has been mentioned but ptl officials have 
said a buyer would need to pay about 100 million for the 
ministrys assets which have been appraised at about 200 million 
</TEXT>
