police arrested 41 protesters in wheelchairs 
sunday after the protesters blocked traffic and disrupted 
activities at a hotel where the american public transit association 
was meeting 
the protest took members of americans disabled for accessible 
public transport 14 blocks from the gateway arch to the omni 
international hotel 
there was little disruption of traffic during the procession 
said police capt clarence harmon but once they reached the hotel 
some of the protesters blocked traffic and others entered the hotel 
authorities said those inside the hotel blocked stairways and 
elevator entrances all 41 were charged with trespassing police 
said 
adapt has said it wants the transit association to push for the 
installation of wheelchair lifts on all public buses in the united 
states rather than invoking federal rules that allow alternative 
transportation such as special vans 
bill bolte a spokesman for adapt said the group planned 
further demonstrations to protest treatment of those arrested 
