the remains of one of three us marines killed 
when their helicopter crashed into the pacific ocean have been 
identified as those of the pilot a marine corps spokesman said 
divers found the remains of capt john e nisbet jr 27 of 
corpus christi texas saturday near the crash site in about 30 
feet of water chief warrant officer eric carlson said sunday 
five days of searching failed to find the remains of the 
copilot 1st lt andrew g first 24 of concord mass and the 
crew chief cpl jeffrey e tokarz 23 of fountain valley calif 
the navy and us coast guard pulled out of the search effort 
sunday but the marine corps will continue looking for first and 
tokarz carlson said 
the three were aboard a ch46 sea knight helicopter that crashed 
wednesday about a mile from the island of oahu 
all major components of the helicopter based at the marine 
corps air station at kaneohe have been found for the investigation 
into the cause of the crash carlson said 
