divers recovered the remains saturday of one of 
three us marines aboard a helicopter that crashed in the pacific 
ocean off the island of oahu a marine corps spokesman said 
the remains were taken by helicopter to tripler army medical 
center in honolulu for identification according to chief warrant 
officer eric carlson 
divers found the remains around 1 pm saturday near the scene 
of the crash which occurred wednesday one mile from shore in about 
30 feet of water carlson said 
meanwhile the search continued for the two other marines aboard 
the ch46 sea knight helicopter from the marine corps air station 
at kaneohe he said 
the three marines have been identified as the pilot capt john 
e nisbet jr 27 of corpus christi texas the copilot 1st lt 
andrew g first 24 of concord mass and the crew chief cpl 
jeffrey e tokarz 23 of fountain valley calif 
the marine navy and coast guard search had located submerged 
pieces of the twinrotor transport helicopter the cause of the 
crash remained under investigation 
