<TEXT>
united rubber workers union members at 
firestone inc plants and offices in six states went on strike 
sunday after negotiators failed to reach a tentative agreement on a 
contract settlement 
they did not meet the pattern settlement negotiated with 
goodyear said urw president milan stone after the 1201 am 
sunday deadline stone confirmed the strike was under way 
stone was referring to a tentative agreement reached by the 
urws international committee with goodyear tire amp rubber co the 
union intended for the agreement to serve as a pattern for other 
rubber companies 
stone said firestones latest proposal did not match the pattern 
settlement in the areas of pension costofliving increases and 
health insurance 
these are the three issues that are very dear to our hearts 
and we will fight to keep those and thats why were on strike 
but firestone officials had a different view of the proposal 
we are deeply distressed that the union has taken this 
action george w aucott firestones executive vice president 
said in a statement we believe that our proposal contains a 
number of improvements and in terms of firestones position in the 
industry is equal in value and in cost to the urw settlement 
proposal 
the urw represents about 4700 workers at firestone plants in 
noblesville ind des moines iowa decatur ill russellville 
ark and oklahoma city okla and offices in akron 
firestone spokesman jim strandberg said none of the plants was 
scheduled to be operating early sunday morning 
talks resumed late saturday in a final effort to avert a strike 
but even as the firestone negotiations continued the fate of the 
pact with goodyear was riding on the outcome of a vote sunday by a 
1668member local in danville va 
goodyears 15000 urw members rejected the tentative contract by 
a 31 ratio may 1 local 831 in danville was to vote on whether to 
reconsider the pact the vote could be pivotal because the danville 
local has enough members to turn the vote around 
six of the 11 goodyear locals approved the pact but they do not 
represent a majority of the goodyear membership in the urw under 
urw bylaws ratification must be made by a majority of the locals 
representing a majority of the membership 
goodyear chairman robert mercer was in danville on friday to 
appeal to union leaders mercer said he met for more than an hour 
with about 15 members of the locals executive board to urge them 
to talk to their people on the floor and seek ratification he 
said the visit and appeal were unique in his experience as chairman 
i felt it the visit was necessary to make sure i fulfilled 
my obligations i cant sit here in akron and keep my fingers 
