<TEXT>
just two years ago the congressional budget 
offices economic forecasts ruled capitol hill and its decisions 
could force the president to cut billions of dollars in federal 
spending 
but the congress has stripped the office of important powers 
left it without a permanent director for more than a year and 
exposed the officially nonpartisan agency to charges of political 
tampering 
cbo is disintegrating said rep william h gray iii dpa 
chairman of the house budget committee 
congress set up its own budget office a dozen years ago to 
counter the power of the presidents office of management and 
budget in the following decade the agency established a 
reputation for nonbiased and unvarnished assessments of the 
federal budget and its workings in the economy 
in december 1985 its power peaked with passage of the emergency 
deficit reduction amendment known as grammrudman the cbo was 
charged with making deficit estimates that once averaged with 
white house figures launched automatic spending cuts across the 
government 
in 1986 however the supreme court found the law defective in 
rewriting the statute congress relegated the cbo to advisory 
status 
a housesenate search committee meantime was unable to agree 
on a replacement for cbo director rudolph g penner whose 
threeyear term was expiring at years end penner stayed on until 
march 1987 
the two sides appear farther apart than ever over choosing a 
successor although there are many qualified candidates each 
chamber is fighting for its own choice 
personal honor is at stake said one house aide involved in 
the process who spoke on the condition of anonymity 
