i want to talk today about the challenge to keep hope alive 
of making it on broken pieces he told students at commencement 
ceremonies for predominantly black hampton university 
among the graduates was gertrude brown whose life of struggle 
was movingly related by her soninlaw jackson 
mrs brown who was an unwed mother as a teenager worked full 
time as she raised five children including daughter jacqueline 
the girl who would grow up to become jacksons wife 
three of her children went on to receive advanced degrees when 
she was 49 mrs brown decided her own time had come she went back 
to get her high school diploma and began her college education 
still working full time she painstakingly took one or two classes 
a semester 
a dozen years later she reached her goal 
she is of strong character and she never surrendered against 
all odds she is graduating today that is what this graduation 
is all about jackson said 
calling up images of determination and pride jackson invoked 
the fight for civil rights 
we worked through blood and smiled through our tears to get to 
this juncture in the road the struggle must continue he told 
the crowd we must not surrender 
jackson urged redefinition of the nations priorities to help 
the poor homeless and powerless he called for more taxes on the 
wealthy and for us allies to assume a greater share of defense 
burdens 
jackson said he would remember his motherinlaws example as he 
campaigned for the democratic presidential nomination 
i will never surrender to the odds said jackson who lags 
far behind the democratic frontrunner michael dukakis he led the 
audience in a chant keep hope alive 
jackson challenged the graduates to help care for those who 
could not help themselves 
i challenge our nation to do justice and to love mercy we 
must keep america strong and make america better how we relate to 
the least of these the children in the dawn of life poor people 
in the pit of life old folks in the sunset of life is a 
measurement of our character jackson told the audience of more 
than 11000 at hampton coliseum 
jackson said as president he would double the federal dollars 
spent on education 
it makes more sense to invest in public education day care 
and prenatal care on the front side of life rather than jail care 
welfare and despair on the back side of life he said 
he also called for raising the minimum wage working to bring 
womens wages in line with those of men and providing universal 
health insurance 
later sunday jackson addressed new jersey democrats who were 
holding their state convention new jerseys primary is june 7 the 
same day as californias 
i havent inherited any voters jackson told the group 
ive earned every vote ive gained 
